We observed some more features not included in the original description of Terayama ( 2004 ), which we describe now: head slightly longer than wide; eye median-sized, very salient; ocellus large; occipital carina illdefined; Notauli complete, slightly convergent; posterior margin of scutellar furrow straight; propodeal disc elongate; paramedian carina conspicuous; callus present; fovea shallow; hypopygium (
Fig. 58
) 1.29 × as long as wide; posterior margin strongly trilobate; median lobe angulate, wide; lateral lobe rectangular, very short; lateral margin parallel; anterior pigmented line defined, slender; median stalk long; lateral stalk present, rectangular, conspicuous. Genitalia (
Figs 93–94
): aedeagus uniformly wide; apical margin of ventral paramere convex; dorsal paramere as wide as ventral one, glabrous; basivolsella excavated; inner margin of cuspis sinuous; genital ring long.
